title: Boat Stick Puncture Test
story: dungeo
description: Test that carrying sharp stick into boat punctures and deflates it

---

# Setup - get pump and stick via GDT
> gdt
[OK: contains "GDT"]

# Give ourselves the lamp
> tk brass lantern
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Give ourselves the pump
> tk hand pump
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Give ourselves the stick
> tk sharp stick
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Teleport to Dam Base where boat is located
> ah Dam Base
[OK: contains "Dam Base"]

> ex
[OK: contains "Returning"]

# Turn on lamp for light
> turn on lantern
[OK: matches /(on|already)/i]

# ============================================================================
# TEST: Inflate boat then board with stick - should puncture
# ============================================================================

> look
[OK: contains "Dam Base"]
[OK: matches /(plastic|boat|pile)/i]

# Inflate the boat
> inflate boat
[OK: matches /(inflate|seaworthy)/i]

# Verify we're still holding the stick
> i
[OK: contains "stick"]

# Try to board the boat with the stick - punctures the boat silently
# The puncture happens via event handler - no explicit message yet
> board boat
[OK: matches /(get in|board|enter)/i]

# Verify the boat is now deflated (the handler worked)
> look
[OK: matches /(pile|plastic)/i]

# ============================================================================
# TEST: The correct way - put stick in boat first
# ============================================================================

# Re-inflate the boat
> inflate boat
[OK: matches /(inflate|seaworthy)/i]

# Put the stick in the boat (not carrying it)
> put stick in boat
[OK: matches /(Done|put|boat)/i]

# Now board the boat - should succeed
> board boat
[OK: matches /(board|enter|get in|boat)/i]

# Verify we're in the boat
> look
[OK: matches /boat|river/i]
